	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64358396"><p><div class="quote"><p>Do modern EVs have a transmission ? I kind of doubt it.</p></div><p>Not transmissions per say, but some EVs do get creative with their drive systems. Teslas for example change which wheels are driven depending on if you're accelerating or just cruising.</p><p>There is talk about a 2 speed gearbox though on performance cars (reads racing) to allow for a greater top speed. But that's sort of not relevant for road cars, and most EVs on the market these days are electrically speed limited which is why you get something like a Polestar 2 standard with 200kW motors, and the Polestar 2 dual motor performance edition with 350kW both have 205km/h top speed but wildly different accelerations and torque figures.</p></div>
	</div>

