		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64358472"><p>If nothing else, any time I've purchased a new car, the manual transmission package was always cheaper for example.</p><p>I also prefer manual transmission, except when I don't (such as driving on exceptionally steep hills, and in stop and go traffic).  In my case it's just what I'm used to.  But I think it far fetched to get a fake shift thing to pretend I'm driving manual.  I'd rather save my money and hum acceleration sounds uncomfortably loud to my passengers every time I accelerate.</p></div>
