<div id="comment_status_64358700" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64358700" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64358700" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64358700" name="comment_link_64358700" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23274788&amp;cid=64358700" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64358700)" >Bollocks</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64358700" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64358700); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81">necro81</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81">( 917438 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64358700">		
		on Sunday March 31, 2024 @10:51AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23274788&amp;cid=64358700">#64358700</a>)
		<small><a href="//slashdot.org/~necro81/journal/" title="Wednesday March 07, 2007 @06:30PM" class="user_journal_display">Journal</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64358700">EVs aren&rsquo;t killing stick shifts, consumers and car companies did.  It&rsquo;s all there in the summary: manual transmissions have been a minority for decades, and today account for a tiny fraction of new car sales.  Don&rsquo;t blame Tesla, or regulators, or any other boogey-man: stick shifts would have been on the same declining trajectory regardless.  Even if some people fancy themselves as Vin Diesel behind the wheel, most drivers are in fact not that skilled or concerned with performance or efficiency.  Whatever the Slashdot crowd wants to say, most drivers are lazy: push the pedal, and the car goes. You want performance, just throw in a bigger engine and some traction control. <br> <br>

 It&rsquo;s much like computing: although the Slashdot crowd bemoans bloated packages, efficient code, 640k is enough for anybody, command line is faster than GUI for &ldquo;real&rdquo; work..  At the end of the day, most end users could not care less, and will purchase a device with higher specs regardless, not caring if it actually does a better delivering YouTube than a machine from 5-10 years ago.<br> <br>

I say this as someone who learned on a manual and drove stick exclusively for decades.  (And still writes C code for microcontroller.) I enjoyed them.  I still enjoy using them when traveling outside the US.  I&rsquo;ve taught my eldest child the basics of how to drive one. But some years ago I replaced my 2.0L stick shift daily driver for a 1.5L CVT hybrid, and cut my fuel usage in half overnight.  My next car will be an EV. So it goes.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64358700">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64358700" class="btn link" href="//tech.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23274788&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64358700" onclick="D2.replyTo(64358700); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
